<br>
Aye, this is my feeling exactly as to the way to approach raids. I always tell anyone that will listen to never expect loot or exp (and expect to lose exp for that matter) on raids. You will never be disapointed that way. Heck, I went to fear a couple of weeks ago with NTB for the hell of it, knowing I would likely get no loot or exp and probably lose exp. I lost a half a blue bub of exp, and never though anything of it. Had a blast and made some new friends.<br>
<br>
As to looting rules, I have no real problem with most of the ideas that are possible, however, I do think the 55+ BP issue should be amended to 50+ and full guild members (no probationaries), with Kael BPs going to 55+ that *do not* have planar. Having a planar BP go to someone on a plane raid, and then a week later having them get a Kael BP is simply a waste and hurts us as a whole. So basically, if you don't have kunark class armor, planar, (of course kael/ss quests armor) then you don't get Kael BP unless everyone 50+ has a BP of that caliber.<br>
<br>
I would also like to suggest that some of these loot rules be amended so that for the *few* people that only show up on Fear or Hate (depending on where their armor drops) and skips the other cannot loot armor till everyone else gets something and they don't get first dibs on legs/bp. There are a few people like that (I won't name names, we probably all know most of the individuals), and they shouldn't be awarded.<br>
<br>
One other thing, I think either the points that items cost should be raised, or the points we receive for attending should be lowered from the proposal, as many of us will end up with a ton of unused points creating a lot of arguments when everyone wants to &quot;buy&quot; the same thing. Hell, maybe the original loot list format can be used, where priority to buy is given to the person highest on the lists. Just some thoughts.<br>
<br>
Abazagaroth Katzkortulu<br>
