<br>
Unfortunately, though, my instincts tell me a system like that is ultimately doomed to fail and cause a lot of arguing and resentment.  I think human nature would lead people to start seeing favouritism (whether it exists or not).  I also think it could put a lot more pressure on guild officers; they're already getting a lot of flak about the unfairness of random rolling and I imagine it would only increase if the officers were personally responsible for who got what loot.<br>
<br>
I think, given the nature of humanity in general, our best bet is an impartial point system that is entirely based on actual numbers.  With points being awarded based only on participation, there is absolutely no question of who &quot;deserves&quot; to win loot because everyone can see for themselves that a particular individual has *earned* the points to win the loot.<br>
<br>
Of course, I could be also be very wrong (it's been known to happen <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  ).  What do the rest of you think about a loot committee? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/ulilasthedragonslayer.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lilas the Dragonslayer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>,,,,</span><br>  Posts: 19<br> <font color=#0000FF>(2/9/02 10:52:55 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fallianceraidforumfrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7.topic&index=33>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: loot system</span><hr size=1> Problem: An invited guest walks away with cleric BP.. Why? Cause he attended that planes raid and assisted. This has happened! and I think we all agree that we don't want this happening.<br>
The 55+ doesnt mean you won't get any loot the &quot;one loot till everyone has something&quot; still aplys even if the 55+ get something. In other words the 55+ has to pass on everthing else to have a chance at BP or legs.. and if  he loots something else his chance at BP/legs has to be passed down.<br>
<br>
All the 55+ rule does is give someone of high lvl, that has gone to probably 3 times as many planes raids as some one under 55, better odds to get what they still need to upgrade on.<br>
