<br>
The 55+ rule is probably a good idea.  I guess what makes me most in favor of it is that if you are 55+ and don't already have at least your planar bp you are really in need.  By the same token I can completely understand the cry of the less than 55 people that having better equipment will allow you to get to 55+ faster.  Azerik is a chronically underequipped warrior.  Slowly over the past few months I have gotten a couple of pieces that have improved him so as to at least get rid of the stuff he has been wearing since level 20 or so, but he still lacks in areas that would make him a better tank and thus benefit all.<br>
<br>
It would be great if I could get a thurg breastplate for him, but if Dinekus is still fighting at his level (58? 56?) and doesen't even have a planar bp then he needs it far more than I do.  I would say that we do need to keep that 55+ rule with some officer discretion in it though.  If we have ToonX that is semi-retired or the owner is playing alts all the time now and only brings ToonX out for occasional exercise but is over 55 it would pain me greatly to see that good bp or legs go to ToonX when someone else could get far more use out of it even if they are under 55.<br>
<br>
The point system that has been proposed as I understand it would award points for showing up to the raid and if you spent part of them on a drop then the remainder would stay in your &quot;bank&quot; until you wanted to use them.  I think this is a good system, it encourages people to show up to raids and build up their point totals or to consider more carefully what bits of armor they want rather than just rolling on everything in order to get something.<br>
<br>
We will be figuring out what constitutes &quot;attendance&quot; at the raid however.  The very nature of this game has us scattered from the west coast of the USA all the way to the UK (don't think we have anyone further out in either direction anymore).  That makes it difficult to find a time when everyone can attend, but there are ways to work around that.  As of now we have people that will have to leave early and people that will come late.  We need to establish some guidelines that say about how long a raid should take (very flexible, but good for a yardstick) and a cutoff time that if you arrive after or leave before you won't be getting points.  It is harsh, but it needs to be that way to keep people from showing up for the first 5 minutes or the last 5 minutes and demanding points when there are people that have been there for 14 hours.<br>
<br>
I just put this up as a &quot;policy&quot; on our site, but will state it here because it applies.  If you want people to come to your events and help you achieve the goals you have then you need to sacrifice your time in &lt;insert favorite hunting ground here&gt; and get out to other peoples raids.  This means slower experience probably since you will be devoting time to helping someone else rather than your own advancement, but it will make it much more likely that the guy you helped with that quest the other day want to show up at your epic raid.<br>
<br>
Guilds in general and alliances in particular are about helping each other to accomplish things we can't do by ourselves.  It means that I need some people to help me kill those giants in WL for the last bit of the phenocryst focus quest so I call on my guildies.  They show up because they want to help, they fight hard, some of them die (hehe, rikko if I remember right), and they pull out the W and help me get my quest finished.  There is no way I could have done that as a necro (or any other class) and lived by myself no matter what level I was.  Now, did they *have* to? no.  But they did because they wanted to help.  I will remember that when one of them needs help finishing one of the ring quests or has a bad spot in a deep dungeon and needs a body or 6 summoned.<br>
<br>
Before I wander any further afield I just want to thank everyone for posting on this, we really need the input as officers to help to establish a policy that pisses the most people off at once..no wait, makes as many people happy as we can, yeah, that's it.  Knowing your feelings on the matter really does help.<br>
<br>
Just remember this is a G A M E, it is supposed to be F U N, if you have lost sight of either of those words I am sure you have a dictionary around somewhere in the house, you might want to refresh.  <br>
<br>
Azerik Bloodletter<br>
Guild leader in search of a good signature... <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fallianceraidforumfrm9.showMessageRange?topicID=7.topic&start=1&stop=20>1</a> <b>2</b> <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fallianceraidforumfrm9.showMessageRange?topicID=7.topic&start=41&stop=42>3</a> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub42.ezboard.com/fallianceraidforumfrm9.showPrevMessage?topicID=7.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub42.ezboard.com/fallianceraidforumfrm9.showNextMessage?topicID=7.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fallianceraidforumfrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7.topic&index=40><img src=http://home.swbell.net/kryson/allireply1.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"><a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fallianceraidforumfrm9.threadControl?topicID=7.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fallianceraidforumfrm9.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=7.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fallianceraidforumfrm9.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=7.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub42.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="allianceraidforumfrm9">General<option value="allianceraidforumfrm7">Planar Raid Schedule & RSVP<option value="allianceraidforumfrm11">Epic Raids<option value="allianceraidforumfrm12">Non-Epic & Non-Planar Events!<option